CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 28, 1970, pg. 11, reads: "Set For Show Down - Friday is the big day for both the Fifth Avenue and Schenley High School basketball teams when they meet in a game that may eventually decide the City League Champions for 1970. Fifth is unbeaten in city league pay and Schenley has lost only once and that to Fifth.  Members of the Fifth team who will be seeing most of the action are shown in left photo.  Left to right. Chris Eleam, Sam Fleming, Milton Miles, Wynorris Banks, Stanley Stevens and Chris Eleam...Harris Photos"
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of six Fifth Avenue High School basketball players, left to right: #11 Chris Eleam, #10 Sam Fleming, #51 Milton Miles, #21 Wynorris Banks, #32 Stanley Stevens, and #15 Dwight Clay, posed in gymnasium
